Definitions: Full text of article, as read by OCR.

Name: ProductLink
Definitions: URL for article.

Name: id
Definitions: Unique article ID including abbreviated title, date of newspaper and article number.

Name: alto
Definitions: Root element.

Name: Description
Definitions: Describes general settings of the ALTO file like measurement units and metadata.

Name: Layout
Definitions: Root layout element.

Name: Styles
Definitions: Styles define properties of layout elements. A style defined in a parent element is used as default style for all related children elements.

Name: xlmns
Definitions: Declares the XML namespace for ALTO.

Name: MeasurementUnit
Definitions: All measurement values inside the ALTO file except font size are related to this unit. The default is 1/10 of mm.

Name: OCRProcessing
Definitions: Container for information about how the text was created, including preprocessing, OCR processing, and postprocessing steps. Where possible, this draws from MIX's change history.

Name: sourceImageInformation
Definitions: Container for information to identify the image file from which the OCR text was created.

Name: fileName
Definitions: Page image filename.

Name: ocrProcessingStep
Definitions: OCR processing step (container).

Name: ID
Definitions: ID for OCR processing.

Name: processingSoftware
Definitions: Container for information about OCR software. Where applicable, the preferred method for determining this information is by selecting Help --> About.

Definitions: A description of any setting of the processing application. For example, for a multi-engine OCR application this might include the engines which were used. Ideally, this description should be adequate so that someone else using the same application can produce identical results.

Name: softwareCreator
Definitions: The name of the organisation or company that created the application.

Name: softwareName
Definitions: The name of the OCR software.

Name: softwareVersion
Definitions: The version of OCR software.

Name: TextStyle
Definitions: Defines font properties of text.

Name: FONTSIZE
Definitions: Font size in points (1/72 of an inch).

Name: FONTSTYLE
MCHOICE Values: bold, italics, subscript, superscript, smallcaps, underline
Definitions: List of any combination of font styles.

Name: FONTTYPE
Definitions: Font type (e.g. serif or sans-serif).

Name: FONTWIDTH
Definitions: Font width type (e.g. proportional or fixed).

Name: ID
Definitions: Relative ID for text style.

Name: Page
Definitions: Container element for page.

Name: PrintSpace
Definitions: Container for rectangle covering the printed area of a page. Page number and running title are not part of the print space.

Name: HEIGHT
Definitions: Dimensions of page expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: ID
Definitions: Page number relative to issue.

Name: PC
Definitions: Confidence level of OCR for the page. A value between 0 (unsure) and 1 (sure).

Name: PHYSICAL_IMG_NR
Definitions: Page number relative to issue.

Name: PROCESSING
Definitions: ID for OCR processing.

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of page expressed in inch1200 (width).

Name: TextBlock
Definitions: Container for text block.

Name: HEIGHT
Definitions: Dimensions of print space expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: HPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of print space expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Name: ID
Definitions: Relative ID for print space.

Name: VPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of print space expressed in pixels (vertical).

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of print space expressed in inch1200 (width).

Name: TextLine
Definitions: Container for single text line.

Name: HEIGHT
Definitions: Dimensions of text block expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: HPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of text block expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Name: ID
Definitions: Relative ID for text block.

Name: language
Definitions: Language of text block. Applies to the contents of the @content attribute on the <STRING> element.

Name: VPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of text block expressed in inch1200 (vertical).

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of text block expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: xmlns:ns1
Definitions: Declares the namespace.

Name: HYP
Definitions: Container for hyphenation char. Can appear only at the end of a line.

Name: SP
Definitions: Container for white space.

Name: String
Definitions: Container for a sequence of chars. Strings are separated by white spaces or hyphenation chars.

Name: HEIGHT
Definitions: Dimensions of text line expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: HPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of text line expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Name: ID
Definitions: Relative ID for text line.

Name: VPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of text line expressed in inch1200 (vertical).

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of text line expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: SUBS_TYPE
Definitions: Indicates word is hyphenated, and which part of the hyphenation is contained.

Name: CONTENT
Definitions: Character content of string.

Name: HEIGHT
Definitions: Dimensions of string expressed in inch1200 (height).

Name: HPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of string expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Name: ID
Definitions: Relative ID for string.

Definitions: Full hyphenated word.

Name: VPOS

Definitions: Confidence level of OCR for the string. A value between 0 (unsure) and 1 (sure).

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of string expressed in inch1200 (width).

Name: HPOS
Definitions: Positional coordinates of string expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Name: VPOS

Name: CONTENT
Definitions: The character content of the string; in this case, always "-".

Definitions: Positional coordinates of hyphen expressed in inch1200 (horizontal).

Definitions: Positional coordinates of hyphen expressed in inch1200 (vertical).

Name: WIDTH
Definitions: Dimensions of hyphen expressed in inch1200 (always width only).

Definitions: Month of publication (numerical).

Definitions: Day of publication (numerical).

Definitions: Edition number as a string "ed-#" (usually #=1, unless the same newspaper publishes a morning and evening edition).

Definitions: XML contents of the page, contained in a file called "ocr.xml".

Name: mets
Definitions: Root element.

Name: mdWrap
Definitions: Container for metadata information.

Name: xmlData
Definitions: Used to specify the type of the wrapped metadata set as an XML fragment.

Name: LABEL
Definitions: Label describing the metadata type. See MDTYPE.

Name: MDTYPE

Definitions: Full text of article in paragraphs, as read by OCR.

Name: title
Definitions: Title of the article.

Name: alto
Definitions: Root element.

Name: Description
Definitions: Describes general settings of the ALTO file like measurement units and metadata.

Name: Layout
Definitions: Root layout element.

Name: Styles
Definitions: Styles define properties of layout elements. A style defined in a parent element is used as default style for all related children elements.

Name: xmlns
Definitions: Declares the XML namespace.

Name: xmlns:xlink
Definitions: Declares the XML namespace.

Name: MeasurementUnit
Definitions: All measurement values inside the ALTO file except font size are related to this unit. The default is 1/10 of mm.

Name: OCRProcessing
Definitions: Container for information about how the text was created, including preprocessing, OCR processing, and postprocessing steps. Where possible, this draws from MIX's change history.

Name: sourceImageInformation
Definitions: Container for information to identify the image file from which the OCR text was created.

Name: fileName
Definitions: Page image filename.

Name: ocrProcessingStep
Definitions: OCR processing step (container).

Name: preProcessingStep
Definitions: OCR processing step (container).

Name: ID
Definitions: ID for OCR processing.

Name: applicationDescription
Definitions: A description of any important characteristics of the application, especially for non-commercial applications. For example, if a non-commercial application is built using commercial components, e.g., an OCR engine SDK, those components should be mentioned here.

Name: processingAgency
Example Content: CCS Content Conversion Specialists GmbH, www.content-conversion.com
Definitions: Identifies the organisation level producer(s) of the processed image.

Name: processingDateTime
Definitions: Date or DateTime the page images were processed.

Name: processingSoftware
Definitions: Container for information about OCR software. Where applicable, the preferred method for determining this information is by selecting Help --> About.

Name: processingStepDescription
Definitions: An ordinal listing of the image processing steps performed on the issue. For example, "image despeckling".

Name: processingStepSettings
Definitions: A description of any setting of the processing application. For example, for a multi-engine OCR application this might include the engines which were used. Ideally, this description should be adequate so that someone else using the same application can produce identical results.

Name: softwareCreator
Example Content: CCS Content Conversion Specialists GmbH, German
Definitions: The name of the organisation or company that created the application.

Name: softwareName
Definitions: The name of the OCR software.

Name: softwareVersion
Definitions: The version of OCR software.

Name: processingSoftware
Definitions: Container for information about OCR software. Where applicable, the preferred method for determining this information is by selecting Help --> About.

Name: softwareCreator
Definitions: The name of the organisation or company that created the application.

Name: softwareName
Definitions: The name of the OCR software.

Name: softwareVersion
Definitions: The version of OCR software.

Name: FONTFAMILY

MCHOICE Values: bold, italics, subscript, superscript, smallcaps, underline

Name: BottomMargin
Definitions: Container for area between the bottom line of letterpress or writing and the bottom edge of the leaf. May contain a page number, signature number or catch word.

Name: LeftMargin
Definitions: Container for area between the print space and the left border of a page. May contain margin notes.

Name: Page
Definitions: Container element for page.

Name: PrintSpace
Definitions: Container for rectangle covering the printed area of a page. Page number and running title are not part of the print space.

Name: RightMargin
Definitions: Container for area between the print space and the right border of a page. May contain margin notes.

Name: TopMargin
Definitions: Container for area between the top line of print and the upper edge of the leaf. It may contain page number or running title.

For a newspaper issue those files typically include page-level images (in TIFF and/or JPEG 2000 format), ALTO XML files describing the layout and content of each individual page, and page-level and/or issue-level PDF files.

Name: ComposedBlock
Definitions: Top-level instance used to contain content for single article on page. Subordinate instances of this element within the article-level <ComposedBlock> represent each article zone within the page. Each zone-level <ComposedBlock> element will contain nested <TextBlock> to contain paragraph text. Additionally, a single <ComposedBlock> will be used to contain nested <ComposedBlock> for illustrations and associated caption text. The illustration and the caption text will be contained within separate zone-level <ComposedBlock> elements within a single parent <ComposedBlock>.

Definitions: Top-level instance used to contain content for single article on page. Subordinate instances of this element within the article-level <ComposedBlock> represent each article zone within the page. Each zone-level <ComposedBlock> element will contain nested <TextBlock> to contain paragraph text. Additionally, a single <ComposedBlock> will be used to contain nested <ComposedBlock> for illustrations and associated caption text. There is a 'similar :cave</span><span> near the source, I believe, of the IMorabool,</span><span> called by the natives " Lall Lall," in which the</span><span> present race of inatives here say a diiMnity dwhelt</span><span> until the " shag-eyed chalk faces" camei and he</span><span> disappeared; and Jonathan, king of the Moorabbol</span><span> tribe, still addresses himself often in supplication</span><span> to an unseen being, whom he says lives in the</span><span> clouds. It is in imitation of the human</span><span> face and figure ; and one of the young men had</span><span> his hair' cut off to adorn the head, and the eye</span><span> brows are composed of the black fine ends of the</span><span> oppossum fur. The figure was interred two or</span><span> three years ago, and the writer, who is acquainted</span><span> with the spot, intends having it exhumed, to be</span><span> sent to the British Museum, to convince many</span><span> that the natives of Australia are not the last ex</span><span> isting link between the animal and the man;</span><span> The reason they give for interring the figure is,</span><span> that they did not wish the fire-water drinkers to</span><span> look upon so sacred a being, and they chose a</span><span> wild unfrequented part for its repose.</span><span> A BACKWOODSMAN.</span></p>
Definitions:
Full text of article, as read by OCR and with all corrections. Article paragraphs are enclosed in a

element. Lines are enclosed by . Article text is not available for some articles, such as those from the Australian Womens Weekly, and articles with a status of "coming soon". For these articles, there will be no articleText element present.

Name: category
MCHOICE Values: Article, Advertising, Detailed lists, results, guides, Family Notices, Literature
Definitions: Category assigned to the article from a pre-defined list.

Name: comment
Example Content: Robert Fuy should probably read Robert Fuz
Definitions: A public comment added to the article. There may be more than one comment element.

Name: commentCount
Definitions: Number of public comments added to this article by Trove users.

Name: correctionCount
Definitions: Number of corrections made to the article. Each correction may involve many lines.

Name: heading
Example Content: Agriculture around Kelvin Grove and Kedron Brook. [BY OUR AGRICULTURAL REPORTER.]

Name: identifier
Definitions: URL for article. This URL leads to the article view on the Trove web interface.

Name: illustrated
Definitions: Indicates if there is an illustration.

Name: lastCorrection
Definitions: Further information about the most recent correction to this article. The correction itself is not included.

Name: list
Definitions: Public, user created lists this article belongs to. There may be more than one list element.

Name: listCount
Definitions: Number of public Trove user created lists this article has been added to.

Name: pdf
Definitions: URL for page. There may be more than one PDF element if the article appears over multiple pages. PDFs are not available for some articles, such as the Australian Women's Weekly, and articles with a status of "coming soon".

Name: relevance
MCHOICE Values: very relevant, likely to be relevant, may have relevance, vaguely relevant
Definitions: Article relevance (multiple choice).

Name: section
Definitions: Section the article appeared in. In the Trove web interface, this is shown on the page view, e.g. http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/page/4824108.

Name: snippet
Example Content: " blue-green plumage holding the tangled loops. A very useful dress it composed of a plaided material "
Definitions: Snippet of article text containing one or more of the search terms. The matching term/s are enclosed in a <B> element.

Name: status
Example Content: "coming soon" (for articles not yet through the QA process)
Definitions: Only included if the article is not currently available. New articles are included before they are fully approved. These articles have a status of "coming soon". They do not include the full text or a link to view the article in Trove. They may be deleted from Trove. If you want to harvest newspaper articles into your own system, you may prefer to only harvest those added more than a month ago, as most articles which are "coming soon" will be approved within this timeframe. If you do harvest any articles which are "coming soon" you will need to check back later to find out whether they still exist/have been approved/get the Trove link and full text.

Name: supplement
Definitions: Section the article appeared in. In the Trove web interface, this is shown on the page view, e.g. http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/page/4824108.

Name: tag
Definitions: Public tag added to the article. There may be more than one tag element.

Name: tagCount
Definitions: Number of public tags added to this article by Trove users.

Name: title
Definitions: Newspaper title (normalised).

Name: trovePageUrl
Definitions: Link to view the first page of this article in the Trove web interface. This is not available for articles with a status of "coming soon".

Name: troveUrl
Definitions: URL for article. This URL leads to the article view on the Trove web interface. If this record was retrieved in response to a search, the search terms will be included in the URL which allows them to be highlighted when viewing in the article. This is not available for articles with a status of "coming soon".

Name: wordCount
Definitions: Word count of article.

Name: article@id
Definitions: Unique article ID.

Name: date
Definitions: Date of publication (article, numerical, YYYY-MM-DD).

Name: edition
Example Content: 2, SPECIAL EDITION TO THE QUEANBEYAN AGE
Definitions: If article appeared in a special newspaper/periodical edition, edition name is included here. In the Trove web interface, this is shown on the page view. e.g. http://trove.nla.gov.au/ndp/del/page/4298413.

Definitions: Page number relative to issue.

Definitions: Unique ID for newspaper. Can be used to look up more details, e.g. http://api.trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/title/42?key=<insert key here>oogle.com/spreadsheets/d/14HY210djglMZDzgeAQK1Q5nAYZiu7e946tHJtei9Gzw/edit#gid=0.

Name: pageLabel
Definitions: Position of page. Sometimes used to indicate what is printed on the page, or perhaps the page number within a section/supplement. Not displayed in the Trove web interface. Sometimes numeric and sometimes not. e.g. http://api.trove.nla.gov.au/newspaper/45649893?reclevel=full&key=<insert key here>.

Definitions: Page number relative to issue (string) and also indicates if the article is part of a supplement/section (displayed in the Trove web interface).

Name: relevance@score
Definitions: Article relevance (numerical). This number can be compared to other search results in this zone, but not to results from other zones.

Name: tag@lastupdated
Definitions: Date stamp of when the tag was added (UTC timezone).

Name: comment@by
Definitions: Username of the person who added the comment.

Name: comment@lastupdated
Definitions: Datestamp of when the comment was most recently added/edited (UTC timezone).

Name: list@by
Example Content: "dance" (NLA staff accounts do not include the "public" prefix)

Definitions: Partial URL to retrieve more information about this list using the Trove API.

Definitions: Username of the person who made the most recent correction to this article, or "anonymous".

Name: lastCorrection@lastupdated
Definitions: Datestamp of when the most recent correction was made to this article (UTC timezone).
